!!!WE WILL DO WHATEVER WE WANT!!!&nbsp;
.This meetup group focuses on application development, with emphasis on cloud, big data, analytics, mobile, social and security. It is geared towards developers and technologists who want to create great apps. To build the next generation of apps we must change: - How we scale apps - How we build and test - Where applications run - How apps communicate - Embrace new ways of thinking Even the definition of what makes an application has changed with Cloud, Mobile and Internet of Things.&nbsp;
.
Our meetups give you the opportunity to get hands on with new and proven technologies to build applications designed for this new world of Cloud, Web, Mobile, Social and Internet of Things. Our Meetups typically include a 45-60 min (max) presentation to provide an introduction to technologies and techniques to help overcome the challenges of building next generation apps. This is usually followed by several hours of hands on experience working alongside fellow developers, and meeting with the developers behind the tools. There is often an opportunity to be among the first to experience alpha/beta technologies . We provide access to all the tools including in the cloud environment. Just bring your&nbsp;laptops. Of course, all our meetups are free to attend and no marketing or sales pitches are permitted.&nbsp;
.
Plans for this Meetup include: - Building production-ready node.js, Java, ASP.net and Ruby using the Cloud - Creating applications and deploying in the Cloud using open platform-as-a-service technology IBM BlueMix - Wiring the Internet of Things to the Cloud using Node-Red, MQTT - Scaling Java applications using WAS Liberty&nbsp;
.HIGHLIGHTS:&nbsp;
+We will be writing codes/apps for Sensor Tags, Raspberry Pi, Parrot Drones etc.&nbsp;
+We will build cognitive apps, that can think like human beings
+We will build apps that plug into social media and analyse data such as twitter feeds, etc.&nbsp; 
+We will compete in challenges and hackathons.&nbsp;
+ WE WILL DO WHATEVER WE WANT!!!

